main event: A UFO was reported in Alexandria, Louisiana on February 23, 1960, observed moving swiftly across the sky.
interesting points: The object was described as a white light brighter than any star, observed for 2-3 seconds.,The object was reported to be flying high and fast in a southwest direction.,The observation was made by a Staff Sergeant from the USAF.,The object was silent with no trail or other indications of being man-made.,The report concluded that the object was likely a natural phenomenon.
witness description: Staff Sergeant from the USAF, credible and capable of making valid observations.
